               <birth when="1843"/>
               <death when="1926-10-20">20 October 1926</death>
               <floruit when="1889">He was the metropolitan of the Ethiopian Orthodox Church,
                  consecrated by <persName ref="PRS3258CyrilIV">Cyril IV</persName>
                  in <date>1889</date>. He arrived to Ethiopia in <date>1881</date>
                  together with the three other bishops: <persName ref="PRS13100Marqos"/>,
                  <persName ref="PRS6404Luqas"/> and <persName ref="PRS7830Petros"/> requested by
                  Emperor <persName ref="PRS10378Yohanne"/>.
                  He was a bishop of <placeName ref="LOC5597Sawa"/> <date notBefore="1881" notAfter="1889">from 1881 to 1889</date>.
                  Following the death of  Emperor <persName ref="PRS10378Yohanne"/> in 1889,
                  when <persName ref="PRS7006Menilek"/> became Emperor he received permission from Coptic patriarch
                  <persName ref="PRS3258CyrilIV"/> and replaced  ʾabuna <persName ref="PRS7830Petros"/> as metropolitan.
               </floruit>
            </person>
